# HighRise Design Token Rules

## Token Structure Cleanup Guidelines

### Platform-Specific Structure Rules

#### Web Components (tokens/web-components/)
- **Remove all schema/metadata**: $schema, $description, name, version, description
- **Use actual component name as root key** (e.g., "input", "button", "tab-item", "textarea") not "component"
- **Remove documentation sections**: responsive, states, variants, types
- **Keep only core token definitions**: size, color, border-radius, container, layout, content, actions
- **Use `description` field** (without $) for individual token descriptions
- **No header structure** - start directly with component tokens

#### Mobile Components (tokens/mobile-components/)
- **REQUIRED header structure**: Include `$comment`, `$description`, and `$component` object at the top
- **$component object structure**:
  ```json
  "$component": {
    "name": "Component Name",
    "description": "Detailed component description",
    "structure": "Visual/DOM hierarchy description",
    "sizes": {
      "sm": "Height and usage context",
      "md": "Height and usage context",
      "lg": "Height and usage context"
    },
    "variants": {
      "default": "Variant description",
      "variant-name": "Variant description"
    },
    "usage": {
      "contexts": "Usage contexts",
      "features": "Key features"
    }
  }
  ```
- **Use `description` field** (without $) for individual token descriptions
- **Prefix descriptions with "Mobile "** for clarity (e.g., "Mobile tab item default background")

### Token Hierarchy Workflow
**CRITICAL**: Always follow this hierarchy:
1. **Check primitive tokens first** - if value doesn't exist, add to primitive tokens
2. **Add to semantic tokens** - create semantic reference to primitive
3. **Reference in component tokens** - use semantic token reference
4. **Never create arbitrary values** - all values must flow through primitive → semantic → component

### Token Reference Patterns (NO "semantic." PREFIX)

#### Colors (use actual primitive structure)
- Primary colors: `{color.primary.blue.600}` (not color.brand.primary)
- Status colors: `{color.secondary.error}`, `{color.secondary.warning}`, `{color.secondary.success}` (not color.status.*)
- Neutral colors: `{color.neutral.gray.100}`, `{color.neutral.gray.700}`
- Background: `{color.background.neutral.subtle.1}`, `{color.background.primary.inactive}`, `{color.background.primary.subtle.0}`
- Text: `{color.text.neutral.body.1}`, `{color.text.primary.title.1}`, `{color.text.error.body.2}`
- Border: `{color.border.neutral.default}`, `{color.border.primary.subtle.2}`, `{color.border.error.moderate.0}`
- Icon: `{color.icon.neutral.info}`, `{color.icon.primary.default}`, `{color.icon.error.moderate}`

#### Transparent Values - ALWAYS Use Semantic Tokens
- **NEVER use raw "transparent"** - always use semantic token reference
- Background transparent: `{color.background.transparent}`
- Border transparent: `{color.border.transparent}`
- Text transparent: `{color.text.transparent}`
- Icon transparent: `{color.icon.transparent}`

#### Border Radius (use actual primitive structure)
- Border radius: `{border.radius.3xs}`, `{border.radius.2xs}`, `{border.radius.xs}`, `{border.radius.sm}`, `{border.radius.md}`, `{border.radius.lg}`, `{border.radius.xl}`, `{border.radius.2xl}`
- Circular borders: `{border.radius.full}` (not specific values)

#### Spacing References (NO "tokens." PREFIX)
**Default approach**: Use direct semantic tokens without unnecessary prefixes
- **Padding tokens**: `{padding.4xs}`, `{padding.3xs}`, `{padding.2xs}`, `{padding.xs}`, `{padding.sm}`, `{padding.md}`, `{padding.lg}`, `{padding.xl}`, `{padding.2xl}`
- **Size tokens**: `{size.3}`, `{size.4}`, `{size.5}`, `{size.6}`, `{size.7}`, `{size.8}`, `{size.9}`, `{size.10}`, `{size.11}`, `{size.12}`, `{size.14}`, `{size.16}`, `{size.20}`, `{size.24}`, `{size.28}`, `{size.32}`, `{size.36}`, `{size.40}`, `{size.44}`, `{size.45}`, `{size.48}`, `{size.56}`, `{size.80}`
- **Height tokens**: `{size.height.3xs}`, `{size.height.2xs}`, `{size.height.xs}`, `{size.height.sm}`, `{size.height.md}`, `{size.height.lg}`, `{size.height.xl}`, `{size.height.2xl}`
- **Use directional tokens when needed**: `{padding.x.3xs}`, `{padding.x.2xs}`, `{padding.x.xs}`, `{padding.x.sm}`, `{padding.x.md}`, `{padding.x.lg}`, `{padding.x.xl}`, `{padding.x.2xl}`, `{padding.y.xs}`, `{padding.y.sm}`, `{padding.y.md}`, `{padding.y.lg}`, `{padding.y.xl}`, `{padding.y.2xl}`, `{gap.3xs}`, `{gap.4xs}`, etc.
- **Mobile component directional padding**: Use `padding.x.default`, `padding.y.default`, and variant-specific padding like `padding.icon-top.top`, `padding.icon-top.bottom`
- **NEVER use "tokens.padding.x" or "tokens.gap.x"** - always use direct references

#### Size Optimization
- **When width and height are same, use single size token**: `{size.3xs}`, `{size.2xs}`, `{size.xs}`, `{size.sm}`, `{size.md}`, `{size.lg}`, `{size.xl}`, `{size.2xl}`
- **For icon sizes, use semantic**: `{size.icon.3xs}`, `{size.icon.2xs}`, `{size.icon.xs}`, `{size.icon.sm}`, `{size.icon.md}`, `{size.icon.lg}`, `{size.icon.xl}`, `{size.icon.2xl}`, `{size.icon.3xl}`, `{size.icon.4xl}`
- **Use numeric**: `{size.24}`, `{size.28}`, `{size.32}`, `{size.36}`, `{size.40}`, `{size.44}`, `{size.48}`, `{size.56}` for specific dimensions

#### Semantic Token Precision
- **Be precise with semantic levels**: Use exact level numbers (0, 1, 2) based on actual design intent
- **Subtle levels**: `subtle.0` (lightest), `subtle.1` (light), `subtle.2` (medium light)
- **Moderate levels**: `moderate.0`, `moderate.1`, `moderate.2`, `moderate.3`
- **Intense levels**: `intense.0`, `intense.1`, `intense.2`
- **Inactive levels**: `inactive`, `inactive.1`, `inactive.2` for disabled states
- **Don't default to level 2** - choose the appropriate level for the specific use case

#### Typography References
- **Font tokens**: `{font.body.regular.3xs}`, `{font.body.regular.2xs}`, `{font.body.regular.xs}`, `{font.body.regular.sm}`, `{font.body.regular.md}`, `{font.body.regular.base}`, `{font.body.regular.2xl}`
- **Font weights**: `{font.body.medium.*}`, `{font.body.semibold.*}` for different weights
- **Heading fonts**: `{font.subheading.semibold.sm}` for larger text
- **Use complete typography tokens**: Include size, weight, and line-height
- **Size-based typography pattern**:
  ```json
  "text": {
    "typography": {
      "3xs": {"value": "{font.body.regular.3xs}", "type": "typography"},
      "2xs": {"value": "{font.body.regular.2xs}", "type": "typography"},
      "xs": {"value": "{font.body.regular.xs}", "type": "typography"},
      "sm": {"value": "{font.body.regular.sm}", "type": "typography"},
      "md": {"value": "{font.body.regular.md}", "type": "typography"},
      "lg": {"value": "{font.body.regular.base}", "type": "typography"}
    }
  }
  ```

### Border Width References
- **Standard border**: `{border.width.default}` (1px)
- **Thick border**: `{border.width.thick}` (2px)
- **Focus ring width**: `{border.width.thick}` for focus indicators

## Component Structural Patterns

### Pattern 1: Color-First Multi-Style Structure (COMPLEX COMPONENTS)
**Best for**: Button-like components with multiple style variants within color variants
**Examples**: button (primary/secondary/tertiary/ghost within each color)

```json
{
  "button": {
    "color": {
      "primary": {
        "primary": {
          "background": {
            "default": {"value": "{color.background.primary.default}", "type": "color"},
            "hover": {"value": "{color.background.primary.intense.1}", "type": "color"},
            "active": {"value": "{color.background.primary.intense.2}", "type": "color"},
            "focused": {"value": "{color.background.primary.intense.1}", "type": "color"},
            "disabled": {"value": "{color.background.primary.subtle.2}", "type": "color"}
          },
          "border": { /* all states */ },
          "text": { /* all states */ },
          "icon": { /* all states */ }
        },
        "secondary": { /* same structure */ },
        "tertiary": { /* same structure */ },
        "ghost": { /* same structure */ }
      },
      "error": { /* same structure with error colors */ },
      "neutral": { /* same structure with neutral colors */ },
      "warning": { /* same structure with warning colors */ },
      "success": { /* same structure with success colors */ }
    },
    "typography": { /* size-based typography */ },
    "border": { /* size-based border radius */ },
    "effects": { /* shadows and focus rings */ },
    "regular": { /* standard button dimensions */ },
    "icon": { /* icon-only button dimensions */ }
  }
}
```

### Pattern 2: Color-Variant Structure (STANDARD COMPONENTS)
**Best for**: Form components, interactive elements with color variants but single style
**Examples**: input, tab-item, input-form

```json
{
  "component-name": {
    "border": {
      "radius": {
        "3xs": {"value": "{border.radius.3xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "2xs": {"value": "{border.radius.2xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "xs": {"value": "{border.radius.xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "sm": {"value": "{border.radius.sm}", "type": "dimension"},
        "md": {"value": "{border.radius.md}", "type": "dimension"},
        "lg": {"value": "{border.radius.lg}", "type": "dimension"}
      },
      "width": {"value": "{border.width.default}", "type": "dimension"}
    },
    "padding": {
      "x": {
        "3xs": {"value": "{padding.2xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "2xs": {"value": "{padding.2xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "xs": {"value": "{padding.xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "sm": {"value": "{padding.xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "md": {"value": "{padding.sm}", "type": "dimension"},
        "lg": {"value": "{padding.md}", "type": "dimension"}
      },
      "y": {"value": "{padding.0}", "type": "dimension"}
    },
    "height": {
      "3xs": {"value": "{size.height.3xs}", "type": "dimension"},
      "2xs": {"value": "{size.height.2xs}", "type": "dimension"},
      "xs": {"value": "{size.height.xs}", "type": "dimension"},
      "sm": {"value": "{size.height.sm}", "type": "dimension"},
      "md": {"value": "{size.height.md}", "type": "dimension"},
      "lg": {"value": "{size.height.lg}", "type": "dimension"}
    },
    "text": {
      "typography": {
        "3xs": {"value": "{font.body.regular.xs}", "type": "typography"},
        "2xs": {"value": "{font.body.regular.sm}", "type": "typography"},
        "xs": {"value": "{font.body.regular.md}", "type": "typography"},
        "sm": {"value": "{font.body.regular.base}", "type": "typography"},
        "md": {"value": "{font.body.regular.2xl}", "type": "typography"},
        "lg": {"value": "{font.body.regular.2xl}", "type": "typography"}
      }
    },
    "icon": {
      "size": {
        "3xs": {"value": "{size.icon.3xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "2xs": {"value": "{size.icon.2xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "xs": {"value": "{size.icon.2xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "sm": {"value": "{size.icon.xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "md": {"value": "{size.icon.xs}", "type": "dimension"},
        "lg": {"value": "{size.icon.xs}", "type": "dimension"}
      }
    },
    "color": {
      "default": {
        "background": {
          "default": {"value": "{color.background.neutral.base}", "type": "color"},
          "hover": {"value": "{color.background.neutral.base}", "type": "color"},
          "filled": {"value": "{color.background.neutral.subtle.0}", "type": "color"},
          "focused": {"value": "{color.background.neutral.base}", "type": "color"},
          "disabled": {"value": "{color.background.neutral.subtle.0}", "type": "color"}
        },
        "border": { /* all states */ },
        "text": { /* all states including placeholder */ },
        "icon": { /* all states */ },
        "focus": {
          "ring": {"value": "{color.border.primary.subtle.2}", "type": "color"},
          "shadow": {"value": "0px 0px 0px 4px rgba(209, 224, 255, 1), 0px 1px 2px 0px rgba(16, 24, 40, 0.05)", "type": "boxShadow"}
        }
      },
      "destructive": { /* same structure with error colors */ }
    }
  }
}
```

### Pattern 3: Layout-Content Structure (INFORMATIONAL COMPONENTS)
**Best for**: Alert-like components with distinct content areas
**Examples**: alert, toast, notification

```json
{
  "alert": {
    "border": {
      "radius": {"value": "{border.radius.2xl}", "type": "borderRadius"}
    },
    "layout": {
      "default": {
        "padding": {"value": "{padding.2xs}", "type": "spacing"},
        "gap": {"value": "{gap.3xs}", "type": "spacing"}
      },
      "inline": {
        "gap": {"value": "{gap.3xs}", "type": "spacing"}
      }
    },
    "content": {
      "gap": {
        "default": {"value": "{gap.4xs}", "type": "spacing"}
      }
    },
    "actions": {
      "gap": {"value": "{gap.2xl}", "type": "spacing"}
    },
    "text": {
      "typography": {
        "title": {
          "default": {"value": "{font.body.semibold.base}", "type": "typography"}
        },
        "supporting": {
          "default": {"value": "{font.body.regular.md}", "type": "typography"}
        }
      }
    },
    "icon": {
      "size": {
        "default": {"value": "{size.icon.md}", "type": "sizing"}
      }
    },
    "close": {
      "size": {
        "default": {"value": "{size.icon.md}", "type": "sizing"}
      },
      "color": {"value": "{color.icon.neutral.moderate.2}", "type": "color"}
    },
    "color": {
      "neutral": {
        "background": {"value": "{color.background.neutral.base}", "type": "color"},
        "border": {"value": "{color.border.neutral.default}", "type": "color"},
        "icon": {"value": "{color.icon.neutral.default}", "type": "color"},
        "text": {
          "title": {"value": "{color.text.neutral.body.1}", "type": "color"},
          "supporting": {"value": "{color.text.neutral.body.2}", "type": "color"}
        }
      },
      "primary": { /* same structure with primary colors */ },
      "success": { /* same structure with success colors */ },
      "error": { /* same structure with error colors */ },
      "warning": { /* same structure with warning colors */ }
    }
  }
}
```

