## Size Naming Standards (UPDATED)

### Extended Size Scale (NOW STANDARD)
**Use consistently across ALL components**:
- `3xs` (3x extra small) - 24px/11px fonts
- `2xs` (2x extra small) - 28px/12px fonts
- `xs` (extra small) - 32px/13px fonts
- `sm` (small) - 36px/14px fonts
- `md` (medium) - 40px/16px fonts
- `lg` (large) - 44px/18px fonts
- `xl` (extra large) - 48px/20px fonts
- `2xl` (2x extra large) - 56px/24px fonts

### Size Implementation Patterns
**Option 1 - Semantic height tokens** (PREFERRED):
```json
"height": {
  "3xs": {"value": "{size.height.3xs}", "type": "dimension"},
  "2xs": {"value": "{size.height.2xs}", "type": "dimension"},
  "xs": {"value": "{size.height.xs}", "type": "dimension"},
  "sm": {"value": "{size.height.sm}", "type": "dimension"},
  "md": {"value": "{size.height.md}", "type": "dimension"},
  "lg": {"value": "{size.height.lg}", "type": "dimension"}
}
```

**Option 2 - Direct size tokens** (when height tokens unavailable):
```json
"height": {
  "3xs": {"value": "{size.24}", "type": "dimension"},
  "2xs": {"value": "{size.28}", "type": "dimension"},
  "xs": {"value": "{size.32}", "type": "dimension"},
  "sm": {"value": "{size.36}", "type": "dimension"},
  "md": {"value": "{size.40}", "type": "dimension"},
  "lg": {"value": "{size.44}", "type": "dimension"}
}
```

**Option 3 - Variant-based height** (for mobile components with layout variants):
```json
"height": {
  "default": {
    "value": "{size.height.2xl}",
    "type": "dimension",
    "description": "Mobile component height for default variant - 56px"
  },
  "top-icon": {
    "value": "{size.height.3xl}",
    "type": "dimension",
    "description": "Mobile component height for top-icon variant - 64px"
  }
}
```

## State Naming Standards (UPDATED)

### Standard Interactive States (REQUIRED)
**Use consistently across ALL interactive components**:
- `default` - Initial/rest state
- `hover` - Mouse hover state  
- `active` - Clicked/pressed state
- `focused` - Keyboard focus state
- `disabled` - Non-interactive state

### Mobile Component States (SIMPLIFIED)
**Mobile components may use simplified state structure**:
- `default` - Initial/rest state
- `active` - Selected/active state
- `disabled` - Non-interactive state
- **Note**: Mobile components typically omit `hover` and `focused` states unless specifically required

### Extended Form States (for form components)
**Additional states for input-like components**:
- `filled` - Input has content/value
- `hover-filled` - Hover state when input has content
- `placeholder` - For placeholder text
- `destructive` - Error/invalid state (alternative to error variant)

### Component-Specific States (when needed)
**For specialized components only**:
- `checked`/`unchecked` - For checkboxes, radios
- `open`/`closed` - For dropdowns, accordions
- `indeterminate` - For checkboxes in partial state

### Focus Ring Implementation (STANDARDIZED)
**All interactive components must include**:
```json
"focus": {
  "ring": {"value": "{color.border.primary.subtle.2}", "type": "color"},
  "shadow": {"value": "0px 0px 0px 4px rgba(209, 224, 255, 1), 0px 1px 2px 0px rgba(16, 24, 40, 0.05)", "type": "boxShadow"}
}
```

